** Rest Api
-> rest (representaional(user or data base) state transfer(inn dono ka matalb hai ki user or
data base kuch information pass karenge))
-> api (application programing interface)
-> Rest Api ka matlab hai ki user ko server(database) se kuch chaiye ye to user ko kuch bhej na hai
server pe to ham direct server me se kuch bhi bhej ya manga nhai shakte hai bhejne ya
manga ne ke liye ham use karte hai rest api ka rest api ki madat se user database se mang
ya bhej shakta hai.
-> abb shamjo ki user ko netflix ka plain chaiye user ne click ki plain ke uppar ok and
apna server ka url hai 23232.34.8080 ok and user ne jise hi click kiya plain ke uppar
to wo 23232.34.8080/netflix/plain iss localhost pe gaya jo apna end point hai plain ka
matalb ki URL hai sird URL ki madat se user plain ko acces nhai kar payega yaha pe chaiey
hoga HTTP (hyper text transfer protocol) matlab user ko UR+HTTP chaiye hoga
** HTTP ke 4 methods hai
1. GET :- user ka data dhekne ke liye get
2. PUT :- user ka data modify karne ke liye put hai
3. POST :- user ka data create karne ke liye post hai
4. DELETE :- user ka data delete karne ke delete method hai

---> REST API = URL + HTTP Verb(get, put, post, delete)

